// useDesignNodeProps
// Derives property values from the current node selection and provides setters with undo support.
// Used by the PropertiesPanel to read and write node properties.

Original values are captured on the first updateProp call per key (before the user's edit) and
cleared when commitProp is called, enabling correct undo deltas.
Originals are also cleared whenever the selection changes to prevent stale entries.

FUNCTION useDesignNodeProps() -> { node, nodes, updateProp, commitProp, updateNodeWithUndo }  EXPORT
  CALLS: useDesignEditorStore (designEditorStore), getEditorRefs (designEditorRefs)
  Derives the list of selected nodes from the store, re-evaluated whenever selectedIds or sceneVersion changes.
  node is the single selected node (null if zero or multiple are selected).

---

FUNCTION updateProp(key, value)
  CALLS: useDesignEditorStore (designEditorStore), getEditorRefs (designEditorRefs)
  Captures the original value of the property (from the live scene graph) on the first call per node per key.
  Applies the new value to all selected nodes immediately (live update, no undo entry yet).

---

FUNCTION commitProp(key)
  CALLS: useDesignEditorStore (designEditorStore)
  Uses the captured original values to create a proper undo entry for the committed property change.
  Clears the stored originals for that key after committing.

---

FUNCTION updateNodeWithUndo(key, value, label?)
  CALLS: useDesignEditorStore (designEditorStore)
  Applies a property change to all selected nodes and records it as a single undoable action.
  Bypasses the two-phase capture/commit pattern — suitable for discrete changes (e.g. dropdown selects).
